              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>ROAS = Total Revenue from Ads / Total Ad Spend. If you spend $10,000 on Google Ads and generate $40,000 in attributable revenue, your ROAS is 4.0 or 400%. The formula is simple; accurate revenue attribution is the hard part.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is target ROAS (tROAS) bidding?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Target ROAS is an automated Google Ads bid strategy where the algorithm adjusts bids in real time to hit a ROAS goal you specify. You set a target (e.g. 400%), and Google's machine learning raises bids when conversion probability is high and lowers bids when it isn't.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
